\"_blank\">Darkmoon Game Prize</a></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Zone:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"/wow-pets/map/darkmoon-balloon/darkmoon_island/\" class=\"zonewithpets\">Darkmoon Island</a></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Approximate Drop Rate:</span>&nbsp;1 in 1,000</p>','N','<p>What better way to celebrate the Darkmoon Faire than a balloon souvenir? The eye painted onto it does seem a bit eerie, though. It\'s almost as if it\'s following me. Nah, that\'s just my imagination... right? Right...?</p>','<p>As of Patch 4.3, the Darkmoon Faire has moved to its very own zone. Tickets earned prior to the patch are unusable.<br /><br /> The new Darkmoon Prize Tickets are obtainable through Darkmoon Faire profession-based quests, dailies, and turning in Darkmoon Faire Artifacts. Check out our <a href=\"http://www.warcraftpets.com/community/forum/viewtopic.php?f=10&amp;t=51\" target=\"blank\">Community Guide: Darkmoon Prize Tickets</a> for more information.</p>','N','N','N',420,1,3,'Y',0,0,0,'N',0,0,0,'N',0,0,0,'N',0,0,0,'N',0,0,0,'N',2263.75,3504,314,1803,0,0,0,'2011-11-29 13:04:58',1,1,1,0,'',3,403000);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (250,337,55215,253,7,40,'N','',0,103125,'Lumpy','lumpy','Lump of Coal','0','blue',20,3,42.586,'','P','Neutral','rock, earth elemental, Feast of Winter Veil, Hillsbrad Foothills','Ground','<p>Rocks tumbling (constant); vocalizations (on-click)</p>','<p>Hovers.</p>','','N','<a href=http://www.wowhead.com/event=141 target=_link>Feast of Winter Veil</a> (December 15-January 2)','N','Y','Y','N','N','N','N','N',0,'lumpy.jpg','wow64/icons/inv/ore/tin_01.png','wow64/icons/inv/ore/tin_01.png','','<p>Right Click to summon and dismiss your coal elemental.</p>','A stowaway from Greatfather Winter\'s workshop, this tiny elemental found himself trapped in a present that was stolen by the Abominable Greench.','|cFFFFD200World Event:|r Feast of Winter Veil','add	1	Quest: You\'re a Mean One...(Alliance)/(Horde)\nadd	2	Approximate Drop Rate: 1 in 65 from [Stolen Present]\nlink	Feast of Winter Veil	http://www.wowhead.com/event=141\nlink	Alliance	http://www.wowhead.com/quest=7043\nlink	Horde	http://www.wowhead.com/quest=6983\nlink	Stolen Present	http://www.wowhead.com/item=116762/stolen-present','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">World Event:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.wowhead.com/event=141\" target=\"_blank\">Feast of Winter Veil</a></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Quest:</span>&nbsp;You\'re a Mean One...(<a href=\"http://www.wowhead.com/quest=7043\" target=\"_blank\">Alliance</a>)/(<a href=\"http://www.wowhead.com/quest=6983\" target=\"_blank\">Horde</a>)</p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Approximate Drop Rate:</span>&nbsp;1 in 65 from [<a href=\"http://www.wowhead.com/item=116762/stolen-present\" target=\"_blank\">Stolen Present</a>]</p>','N','<p>Who says receiving a lump of coal for the holidays has to be a bad thing? I\'ve been extra naughty this year in the hopes that I\'d be more likely to receive this little guy. Here\'s hoping!</p>','<p>The quest, <em>You\'re a Mean One...</em>, is a daily quest that can be completed once per day during the Feast of Winter Veil. Upon completion, players are awarded with a <a href=\"http://www.wowhead.com/item=73792\" target=\"blank\">Stolen Present</a> which has a chance of dropping this companion pet.</p>','Y','Y','N',801,1,7,'Y',453,2,3,'Y',628,4,7,'Y',621,10,7,'Y',814,15,7,'Y',644,20,10,'Y',2336.25,3143,341,765,302,412,0,'2011-12-15 07:04:03',1,1,1,0,'',3,403000);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (251,341,55571,0,6,86,'N','',0,104047,'Lunar Lantern','lunar-lantern','Lunar Lantern','0','blue',20,2,43.0976,'','U','Alliance','blue, lunar festival, lamp, Chinese New Year, Moonglade','Air (flies alongside flying mount)','<p>Vocalizations (on-click)</p>','<p>Hovers about.</p>','','N','<a href=http://www.wowhead.com/event=327 target=_link>Lunar Festival</a> (January 22-February 11)','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',0,'lunar_lantern.jpg','wow64/icons/achievement/worldevent/lunar.png','wow64/icons/inv/shield/26.png','','<p>Right Click to summon and dismiss your Lunar Lantern.</p>','These magical lanterns are acquired at the Lunar Festival, which celebrates the defeat of the Burning Legion by the free races of Azeroth.','|cFFFFD200World Event:|r Lunar Festival|n|cFFFFD200Vendor: |rValadar Starsong|n|cFFFFD200Zone: |rMoonglade|n|cFFFFD200Cost: |r50|TINTERFACE\\ICONS\\INV_Misc_ElvenCoins:0|t','link	Lunar Festival	http://www.wowhead.com/event=327\nlink	Valadar Starsong	http://www.wowhead.com/npc=15864\nzones	Moonglade	Moonglade','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">World Event:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.wowhead.com/event=327\" target=\"_blank\">Lunar Festival</a></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Vendor:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.wowhead.com/npc=15864\" target=\"_blank\">Valadar Starsong</a></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Zone:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"/wow-pets/map/lunar-lantern/moonglade/\" class=\"zonewithpets\">Moonglade</a></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Cost:</span>&nbsp;50<a href=\"http://www.wowhead.com/item=21100\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"/images/wow16/icons/inv/misc/elvencoins.png\" style=\"vertical-align:middle;\" alt=\"Coin of Ancestry\" title=\"Coin of Ancestry\"/></a></p>','N','<p>I absolutely love the Lunar Festival — the dazzling lights, the delicious foods, and the festive clothing. So I\'m excited to finally have a companion that matches my Festive Purple Dress! Goes great with my earrings, too, don\'t you think?</p>','<p>The Horde version of this pet is the <a href=\"/go.asp?pet=252\">Festival Lantern</a>.<br /><br /> Because this pet is Bind on Use, it is possible to learn both versions of the Lunar Festival companions on a single character.</p>','Y','Y','N',114,1,6,'Y',460,2,6,'Y',751,4,1,'N',113,10,7,'Y',463,15,6,'Y',461,20,6,'Y',2059,3088,314,785,290,417,0,'2012-01-22 10:50:45',1,1,1,0,'',3,403000);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (252,342,55574,0,6,86,'N','',0,104049,'Festival Lantern','festival-lantern','Festival Lantern','0','blue',30,2,37.8483,'','U','Horde','red, lunar festival, lamp, Chinese New Year, Moonglade','Air (flies alongside flying mount)','<p>Vocalizations (on-click)</p>','<p>Hovers about.</p>','','N','<a href=http://www.wowhead.com/event=327 target=_link>Lunar Festival</a> (January 22-February 11)','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',0,'festival_lantern.jpg','wow64/icons/achievement/worldevent/lunar.png','wow64/icons/inv/shield/26.png','','<p>Right Click to summon and dismiss your Festival Lantern.</p>','The light from each lantern honors the soul of an ancestor spirit. During the Lunar Festival, these ghostly elders pass along their wisdom to the current generation.','|cFFFFD200World Event:|r Lunar Festival|n|cFFFFD200Vendor: |rValadar Starsong|n|cFFFFD200Zone: |rMoonglade|n|cFFFFD200Cost: |r50|TINTERFACE\\ICONS\\INV_Misc_ElvenCoins:0|t','append	3	(unlimited supply)\nlink	Lunar Festival	http://www.wowhead.com/event=327\nlink	Valadar Starsong	http://www.wowhead.com/npc=15864\nzones	Moonglade	Moonglade','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">World Event:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.wowhead.com/event=327\" target=\"_blank\">Lunar Festival</a></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Vendor:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.wowhead.com/npc=15864\" target=\"_blank\">Valadar Starsong</a></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Zone:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"/wow-pets/map/festival-lantern/moonglade/\" class=\"zonewithpets\">Moonglade</a></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Cost:</span>&nbsp;50<a href=\"http://www.wowhead.com/item=21100\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"/images/wow16/icons/inv/misc/elvencoins.png\" style=\"vertical-align:middle;\" alt=\"Coin of Ancestry\" title=\"Coin of Ancestry\"/></a> (unlimited supply)</p>','N','<p>This lantern just screams \"feng shui!\" It\'s the perfect balance of beauty and function. Like other <a href=\"search/?find=lamp\">floating lanterns</a>, it illuminates my way so I can collect even more of Azeroth\'s adorable companions. I just wish the battery held a longer charge...</p>','<p>The Alliance version of this pet is the <a href=\"/go.asp?pet=251\">Lunar Lantern</a>.<br /><br /> Because this pet is Bind on Use, it is possible to learn both versions of the Lunar Festival companions on a single character.</p>','Y','Y','N',114,1,6,'Y',460,2,6,'Y',751,4,1,'N',113,10,7,'Y',463,15,6,'Y',461,20,6,'Y',2105.5,3232,290,1176,262,579,0,'2012-01-22 10:50:59',1,1,1,0,'',3,403000);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (253,333,54730,333,1,90,'N','',72134,102317,'Gregarious Grell','gregarious-grell','Grell Moss','0','blue',40,3,19.3381,'ccg / code','P','Neutral','green, warlock, imp, demon, tcg','Ground','<p>Pit-pattering footsteps; vocalizations (on-click)</p>','<p>Does flips when idle.</p>','','N','','N','N','N','N','N','Y','N','N',0,'gregarious_grell.jpg','wow64/icons/inv/misc/herb_06.png','wow64/icons/spell/shadow/summonimp.png','','<p>Right Click to summon and dismiss your grell.</p>','The grell are embodiments of the wild side of nature. Tame ones are very rare.','|cFFFFD200Trading Card Game:|r Crown of the Heavens','','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Trading Card Game:</span>&nbsp;Crown of the Heavens</p>','N','<p>I don\'t know about you, but I\'d much rather keep company with a Gregarious Grell than an Impetuous Imp or a Disdainful Demon, don\'t you think?</p>','<p>This pet is redeemed through the common \'Viscous Grell\' loot card from the World of Warcraft <em>Crown of the Heavens</em> TCG expansion. The card may be scratched to reveal a code allowing access to this pet. The code may be redeemed at Blizzard\'s <a href=\"http://www.worldofwarcraft.com/misc/promotion.html\" target=\"blank\">promotion retrieval page</a>. The pet may be obtained in-game from <a href=\"http://www.thottbot.com/?n=1032686\" target=\"blank\">Landro Longshot</a> in Booty Bay.</p>','Y','Y','N',111,1,1,'Y',178,2,7,'Y',173,4,7,'N',113,10,7,'Y',764,15,6,'N',763,20,6,'N',2156,3161,306,1066,339,548,0,'2012-02-01 13:27:38',1,1,1,0,'',3,403000);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (254,347,58163,0,2,38,'N','',0,110029,'Soul of the Aspects','soul-of-the-aspects','Soul of the Aspects','0','blue',30,3,32.3549,'store','P','Neutral','dragon, golden, store','Air (flies alongside flying mount)','<p>Vocalizations (on-click)</p>','<p>Jumps up and twirls, occasionally flies in a star pattern, does a loop and blows a small puff of fire, and flies in a swirl formation.<br /><br /> » #yt#<a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=22lcmUlzmr8\" target=\"blank\">Video</a></p>','','N','','N','N','N','N','N','N','Y','N',0,'soul_of_aspects.jpg','wow64/icons/inv/pet/chromaticdragon.png','wow64/icons/inv/pet/chromaticdragon.png','','<p>Right Click to summon or dismiss the Soul of the Aspects.</p>','The Soul of the Aspects is said to be possessed of mercurial moods ranging from stoic and deliberate to unpredictable and erratic, to loving and deeply pensive.','|cFFFFD200In-Game Shop|r','inline	In-Game Shop	Pet Store','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Pet Store</span>&nbsp;</p>','N','<p>I never knew a Dragon Aspect\'s soul would be this lively. Wait, you\'re telling me there\'s also a Demon soul? N-n-no thank you! One companion\'s soul is enough for me!</p>','<p>This pet is available for digital download exclusively from the <a href=\"http://us.blizzard.com/store/browse.xml?f=c:5,c:33\" target=\"blank\">Blizzard Store</a>. It may be purchased using any major credit card. Players who purchase this pet will receive a code which may be redeemed on any WoW account. All WoW accounts (of the same region) under one Battle.net will have access to this pet. Codes may also be purchased as gifts for other players.</p>','Y','N','Y',429,1,8,'Y',404,2,7,'Y',769,4,1,'Y',115,10,2,'Y',490,15,1,'N',753,20,7,'Y',2286.75,2779,419,863,343,471,0,'2012-04-11 11:59:22',1,1,1,0,'',3,500010);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (255,346,56266,0,4,88,'N','',0,105633,'Fetish Shaman','fetish-shaman','Fetish Shaman\'s Spear','0','blue',50,3,7.1682,'sp / blzce','B','Neutral','shamman, diablo 3, diablo iii, collector\'s edition, collectors edition','Ground','<p>Pit-pattering footsteps; vocalizations (periodic and on-click)</p>','<p>Waves torch back and forth, occasionally leaps into the air and creates floating fiery claw marks.<br />» #yt#<a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=myx4HM0YER4\" target=\"blank\">Video</a></p>','','N','','N','N','N','N','N','Y','N','N',0,'fetish_shaman.jpg','wow64/icons/inv/spear/05.png','wow64/icons/inv/spear/05.png','','<p>Right Click to summon and dismiss your Fetish Shaman.</p>','Fetish shaman are empowered by the spirits of their fallen ancestors. These malevolent spirits are bound to the shaman\'s tribal spear. Control this spear, and you control the shaman.','|cFFFFD200Promotion:|r Diablo 3 Collector\'s Edition','','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Promotion:</span>&nbsp;Diablo 3 Collector\'s Edition</p>','N','<p>Yay! Another critter from the world of Diablo to attend my D3 launch party! Let\'s just hope he\'s better behaved than <a href=\"/wow-pets/humanoid/miscellaneous/mini-tyrael/\">Mini Tyrael</a> and <a href=\"/wow-pets/magic/demons/mini-diablo/\">Mini Diablo</a>. Those two are always at each other\'s throats...</p>','<p>This pet is a free gift for purchasing the Diablo III Collector\'s Edition. This edition was sold in stores (in limited quantity), but it can also be found on auction websites starting the week of May 15, 2012.</p>','Y','N','Y',210,1,4,'Y',178,2,7,'Y',763,4,6,'N',501,10,2,'Y',592,15,6,'N',476,20,4,'N',1982.25,2794,383,1242,310,572,0,'2012-05-15 01:18:21',1,1,1,0,'',3,500010);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (256,665,54745,665,5,26,'N','',72153,102353,'Sand Scarab','sand-scarab','Sand Scarab','0','blue',40,3,16.991,'ccg / code','P','Neutral','bug, beetle, gold, tcg','Ground','<p>Pit-pattering footsteps; vocalizations (on-click)</p>','<p>Idles about.</p>','','N','','N','N','N','N','N','Y','N','N',0,'sand_scarab.jpg','wow64/icons/inv/scarab/clay.png','wow64/icons/inv/scarab/clay.png','','<p>Right Click to summon and dismiss your Sand Scarab.</p>','Easily mistaken for a common beetle, the sting of a sand scarab will quickly clear up the misconception should you be unlucky enough to be stung by one.','|cFFFFD200Trading Card Game: |rTomb of the Forgotten|n','','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Trading Card Game:</span>&nbsp;Tomb of the Forgotten</p>','N','<p>I made a trip to Uldum recently. While I expected to come home with souvenirs, never did I imagine finding this little fella stowed-away in my luggage!</p>','<p>This pet is redeemed through the common \'Sand Scarab\' loot card from the World of Warcraft <em>Tomb of the Forgotten</em> TCG expansion. The card may be scratched to reveal a code allowing access to this pet. The code may be redeemed at Blizzard\'s <a href=\"http://www.worldofwarcraft.com/misc/promotion.html\" target=\"blank\">promotion retrieval page</a>. The pet may be obtained in-game from <a href=\"http://www.thottbot.com/?n=1032686\" target=\"blank\">Landro Longshot</a> in Booty Bay.</p>','Y','Y','N',119,1,5,'Y',155,2,8,'Y',706,4,5,'Y',193,10,5,'Y',283,15,5,'N',519,20,5,'N',1363.25,2524,219,617,246,350,0,'2012-06-12 07:59:25',1,1,1,0,'',3,500010);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (257,671,63832,0,5,35,'N','',0,124660,'Lucky Quilen Cub','lucky-quilen-cub','Lucky Quilen Cub','0','blue',20,3,43.5094,'mopx / mopce','A','Neutral','mythical dog, lion, brown, collector\'s edition, collectors edition','Ground','<p>Vocalizations (on-click)</p>','<p>Barks and rolls over.</p>','','N','','N','N','N','N','N','Y','N','N',0,'lucky_quilen_cub.jpg','wow64/icons/inv/quilinpet.png','wow64/icons/inv/quilinpet.png','','','Offspring of the Imperial Quilen.','|cFFFFD200Promotion:|r Mists of Pandaria Collector\'s Edition Pet','','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Promotion:</span>&nbsp;Mists of Pandaria Collector\'s Edition Pet</p>','N','','<p>This pet is a free gift for purchasing The Mists of Pandaria Collector\'s Edition. This edition was sold in stores (in limited quantity), but it can also be found on auction websites starting the week of September 25, 2012. Purchasing the Digital Deluxe version of Mists of Pandaria also rewards this pet.</p>','Y','N','Y',110,1,8,'Y',576,2,5,'N',159,4,8,'Y',253,10,5,'Y',578,15,5,'N',377,20,8,'Y',1625.75,2339,355,883,299,478,0,'2012-08-29 15:26:47',1,1,1,0,'Check animation; check sound',4,500010);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (258,848,59358,137,5,28,'N','',0,114090,'Darkmoon Rabbit','darkmoon-rabbit','Darkmoon Rabbit','0','purple',40,3,15.4057,'','U','Neutral','white, bloody bunny, monty python, Darkmoon Island','Ground','<p>Vocalizations (on-click)</p>','<p>Grooms face and scratches ear.</p>','','N','<a href=\"http://www.wowhead.com/darkmoon-faire\" target=\"_blank\">Darkmoon Faire</a>','N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',0,'darkmoon-rabbit.jpg','wow64/icons/inv/jewelcrafting/crimsonhare.png','wow64/icons/inv/jewelcrafting/crimsonhare.png','','Right Click to summon and dismiss your Darkmoon Rabbit.','This rabbit is much stronger than it looks.','|cFFFFD200Drop: |rDarkmoon Rabbit|n|cFFFFD200Zone: |rDarkmoon Island','append	0	[??+]\nadd	2	Drop Rate: 1 in 1\nlink	Darkmoon Rabbit	http://www.wowhead.com/npc=58336\nzones	Darkmoon Island	Darkmoon Island','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Drop:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.wowhead.com/npc=58336\" target=\"_blank\">Darkmoon Rabbit</a> [??+]</p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Zone:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"/wow-pets/map/darkmoon-rabbit/darkmoon_island/\" class=\"zonewithpets\">Darkmoon Island</a></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Drop Rate:</span>&nbsp;1 in 1</p>','N','','<p>The Darkmoon Rabbit mob spawns in a cave on the Darkmoon Island, which is accessible only when the Darkmoon Faire is open. This mob is an elite raid boss that has roughly 174,454,800 health. Players will receive the achievement <a href=\"http://mop.wowhead.com/achievement=6332\" target=\"_blank\">That Rabbit\'s Dynamite!</a> after defeating the rabbit.<br /><br />The Darkmoon Rabbit is a reference to the Rabbit of Caerbannog in the film <i><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monty_Python_and_the_Holy_Grail\" target=\"_blank\">Monty Python and the Holy Grail</i>.</p>','Y','Y','N',119,1,5,'Y',851,2,5,'Y',159,4,8,'Y',849,10,8,'Y',312,15,1,'N',163,20,5,'Y',1894,2529,355,1771,366,1058,0,'2012-09-02 10:26:28',1,1,1,0,'',4,500010);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (259,1073,16445,107,1,62,'N','139',0,28487,'Terky','16445','White Murloc Egg','0','blue',30,3,25.8626,'','B','Neutral','murlok, Borean Tundra','Ground','<p>Vocalizations (on-click)</p>','<p>Dances donning a top hat and cane.</p>','','N','','N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',0,'terky.jpg','wow64/icons/inv/egg/03.png','wow64/icons/inv/pet/babymurlocs_white.png','','<p>Right Click to summon and dismiss Terky the baby murloc.</p>','Terky is as shy as she is adorable, preferring the company of close friends over new ones.','|cFFFFD200Drop:|r White Murloc Egg','add	1	Zone: Borean Tundra [68-72]\nadd	2	Drop Rate: 1 in 1\nlink	White Murloc Egg	http://www.wowhead.com/object=244447/white-murloc-egg','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Drop:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.wowhead.com/object=244447/white-murloc-egg\" target=\"_blank\">White Murloc Egg</a></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Zone:</span>&nbsp;Borean Tundra [68-72]</p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Drop Rate:</span>&nbsp;1 in 1</p>','N','<p>A clone of the illustrious Lurky, Terky may well be the rarest pet in Azeroth. I know I\'ve never seen one. No one I know has seen one. Heck, even other murlocs have never seen one. But it\'s in the Pet Journal, so it must exist, right?</p>','This pet was briefly available through an iCoke promotion that coincided with the release of World of Warcraft in Taiwan. Rumors indicate that the pet was not intended to go live and its introduction into the game may have been accidental.<br><br> As of Patch 6.2.2, Terky was re-released in-game as a drop from a hidden treasure.<br><br>You can collect this pet by looting an egg found inside an obscure cave. The entrance of this cave can be found in the water off the coast of <a href=\"http://www.wowhead.com/maps?data=3537:550881\" target=\"_blank\">Riplash Ruins</a> in southern Borean Tundra. For those using coordinates, it\'s located at 55,88. There is a large white pillar and some seaweed at the opening of the cave.<br><br>Inside the cave you\'ll find a lootable egg in a pile of rocks on the ground next to a large white pearl.<br><br> Read more about this pet in our <a href=\"http://www.warcraftpets.com/news/terky-pet-of-the-month-november-2015/\">Pet of the Month</a>!','Y','N','Y',111,1,1,'Y',756,2,9,'Y',350,4,1,'N',193,10,5,'Y',757,15,5,'N',163,20,5,'Y',1557.25,2095,417,800,305,399,0,'2012-09-07 10:27:32',1,1,1,0,'',5,204000);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (260,69,7554,68,3,55,'Y','99',0,0,'Snowy Owl','snowy-owl','','0','',20,0,52.4592,'','','Neutral','white, Winterspring','Ground (hovers)','<p>Vocalizations (on-click)</p>','<p>Flutters about.</p>','','Y','','N','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',0,'snowy-owl.jpg','','wow64/icons/ability/eyeoftheowl.png','','','Winterspring\'s furbolg prize the brilliant white feathers of these majestic creatures for ritual purposes.','|cFFFFD200Pet Battle: |rWinterspring|n|cFFFFD200Season: |rWinter','petzones	0	','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Pet Battle:</span>&nbsp;[17-18] <a href=\"/wow-pets/map/snowy-owl/winterspring/\" class=\"zonewithpets\">Winterspring</a></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Season:</span>&nbsp;Winter</p>','N','','<p>This wild pet spawns in Winterspring but only during winter months.<br><br>Starts spawning: December 21<br>\r\nStops spawning: March 20\r\n\r\n<br><br>Although it was first spotted November 1, 2012 and continued to spawn until March 1, 2013, Blizzard has since changed the spawning of this pet to correspond with the Northern Hemisphere real-world seasons. This means the Snowy Owl will begin spawning at the start of the winter solstice.<br><br> Read more about this pet in our <a href=\"http://www.warcraftpets.com/news/snowy-owl-pet-of-the-month-january-2015/\">Pet of the Month</a>!</p>','Y','N','N',112,1,3,'Y',784,2,2,'Y',517,4,3,'Y',184,10,3,'Y',190,15,3,'Y',518,20,3,'Y',1324.5,1999,328,718,294,387,0,'2012-09-25 00:00:00',1,1,1,0,'Check mobility; Check where it spawns; check sound',4,112010);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (263,348,59020,348,4,80,'N','',0,112994,'Eye of the Legion','eye-of-the-legion','Eye of the Legion','0','blue',40,3,17.4383,'ccg','P','Neutral','green eyeball, warlock pet, tcg','Ground (hovers)','<p>Vocalizations (on-click)</p>','<p>Hovers about.</p>','','N','','N','N','N','N','N','Y','N','N',0,'eye-of-the-legion.jpg','wow64/icons/spell/shadow/evileye.png','wow64/icons/spell/shadow/evileye.png','','<p>Right Click to summon and dismiss an Eye of the Legion.</p>','Always watching. Always judging.','|cFFFFD200Trading Card Game: |rTimewalkers: War of the Anicents|n','','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Trading Card Game:</span>&nbsp;Timewalkers: War of the Anicents</p>','N','','<p>This pet is redeemed through the common \'Eye of the Legion\' loot card from the World of Warcraft <em>Betrayal of the Guardian</em> TCG expansion. The card may be scratched to reveal a code allowing access to this pet. The code may be redeemed at Blizzard\'s <a href=\"http://www.worldofwarcraft.com/misc/promotion.html\" target=\"blank\">promotion retrieval page</a>. The pet may be obtained in-game from <a href=\"http://www.thottbot.com/?n=1032686\" target=\"blank\">Landro Longshot</a> in Booty Bay.</p>','Y','Y','N',210,1,4,'Y',468,2,4,'Y',751,4,1,'N',475,10,6,'Y',323,15,6,'Y',476,20,4,'N',1651.5,2242,352,1261,309,633,0,'2012-09-25 00:00:00',1,1,1,0,'Check mobility; check loot card name; check animation; check sound',4,500010);
