INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (659,1524,86081,1154,6,69,'N','',0,170269,'Netherspawn, Spawn of Netherspawn','netherspawn-spawn-of-netherspawn','Netherspawn, Spawn of Netherspawn','U','blue',20,3,55.2849,'','P','Neutral','slime, Nagrand (Draenor)','Ground','Bubbling (constant)','Bobs back and forth.','','N','','N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',0,'netherspawn-spawn-of-netherspawn.jpg','wow64/icons/spell/nature/acid_01.png','wow64/icons/spell/nature/acid_01.png','','','This slime has a long and confusing lineage.','|cFFFFD200Drop:|r Netherspawn|n|cFFFFD200Zone:|r Nagrand|n','append	0	[99]\nadd	2	Drop Rate: 1 in 1\nlink	Netherspawn	http://wod.wowhead.com/npc=83401\ninline	Nagrand	Nagrand (Draenor)\nzones	Nagrand (Draenor)	Nagrand (Draenor)','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Drop:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/npc=83401\" target=\"_blank\">Netherspawn</a> [99]</p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Zone:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"/wow-pets/map/netherspawn-spawn-of-netherspawn/nagrand_draenor_/\" class=\"zonewithpets\">Nagrand (Draenor)</a></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Drop Rate:</span>&nbsp;1 in 1</p>','N','','Netherspawn is a rarespawn located in a pond of water just south of Oshu\'gun in southwestern Nagrand (Draenor).<br><br>Players can loot this pet from the rare only once per character.','Y','Y','N',608,1,6,'Y',1231,2,6,'N',380,4,8,'N',449,10,4,'Y',450,15,6,'Y',448,20,9,'Y',0,0,338,526,322,258,0,'2014-10-14 00:00:00',1,1,1,0,'',5,600010);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (660,1530,86422,1530,4,79,'N','',0,170274,'Frostwolf Ghostpup','frostwolf-ghostpup','Frostwolf Ghostpup','U','green',20,3,42.3271,'arch','P','Neutral','archaeology','Ground','Vocalizations (on-click)','Sniffs the ground and scratches itself.','','N','','N','N','N','Y','N','N','N','N',0,'frostwolf-ghostpup.jpg','wow64/icons/inv/jewelry/frostwolftrinket_02.png','wow64/icons/inv/pet/frostwolfpup.png','','','The little wolf told to stay.rnWatching, waiting, for vacant prey.rnToo proud to leave, she slipped away.rnUnburdened now, forever free to play.','|cFFFFD200Profession:|r Archaeology','append	0	- Draenor Clans\nadd	1	Artifact: [Frostwolf Ghostpup]\nlink	Frostwolf Ghostpup	http://wod.wowhead.com/item=117380','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Profession:</span>&nbsp;Archaeology - Draenor Clans</p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Artifact:</span>&nbsp;[<a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/item=117380\" target=\"_blank\">Frostwolf Ghostpup</a>]</p>','N','','<p>This companion is a rare tier Draenor Clans archaeology item. It is created by discovering and \"solving\" 175 Draenor Clans Archaeology Fragments. Players may utilize up to three <a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/item=108439\" target=\"blank\">Draenor Clan Orator Cane</a> to aid in the solving of this item. Each Draenor Clan Orator Cane is the equivalent of 20 Draenor Clans Archaeology Fragments.<br /><br /> Once completed, an entry on the Frostwolf Ghostpup can be found in players\' archaeology tab: <em>\"In life, no two creatures will share a stronger relationship than that of a Frostwolf orc and his or her companion wolf. The two eat, sleep, and fight side by side until one or both dies an honorable death. Even then, sometimes not even death itself can stop a frostwolf from coming to the aid of its beloved orc.\"</em></p>','Y','Y','N',119,1,5,'Y',1344,2,5,'N',1047,4,1,'N',1371,10,5,'Y',1397,15,4,'N',654,20,4,'Y',0,0,443,984,363,480,0,'2014-10-14 00:00:00',1,1,1,0,'',5,600010);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (661,1531,86420,1531,10,74,'N','',0,172632,'Ancient Nest Guardian','ancient-nest-guardian','Ancient Nest Guardian','U','green',30,3,35.1746,'arch','P','Neutral','construct, archaeology','Ground','Pit-pattering footsteps; vocalizations (on-click)','Occasionally extends arms and cracks knuckles.','','N','','N','N','N','Y','N','N','N','N',0,'ancient-nest-guardian.jpg','wow64/icons/inv/eng/gizmo1.png','wow64/icons/inv/eng/clockworkegg.png','','','The ancient nest guardian was designed with the unthinkable in mind: to hate cats.','|cFFFFD200Profession:|r Archaeology','append	0	- Arakkoa\nadd	1	Artifact: [Ancient Nest Guardian]\nlink	Ancient Nest Guardian	http://wod.wowhead.com/item=117354','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Profession:</span>&nbsp;Archaeology - Arakkoa</p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Artifact:</span>&nbsp;[<a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/item=117354\" target=\"_blank\">Ancient Nest Guardian</a>]</p>','N','','<p>This companion is a rare tier Arakkoa archaeology item. It is created by discovering and \"solving\" 250 Arakkoa Archaeology Fragments. Because players can only have a maximum of 200 fragments for each branch of Archaeology, 3 <a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/item=109585\" target=\"blank\">Arakkoa Ciphers</a> are necessary to complete the artifact. Each Arakkoa Cipher is the equivalent of 20 Arakkoa Archaeology Fragments.<br /><br /> Once completed, an entry on the Ancient Nest Guardian can be found in players\' archaeology tab: <em>\"Harnessing the power of the sun as a never-ending fuel, these constructs were originally built as automated caretakers for young Arakkoa. With the conflict escalating between the Adherants of Ruhkmar and the Outcasts, many have been repurposed as instruments of war.\"</em></p>','Y','Y','N',384,1,10,'Y',392,2,10,'N',1398,4,3,'Y',455,10,10,'Y',400,15,7,'Y',459,20,10,'Y',0,0,390,1886,345,1031,0,'2014-10-14 00:00:00',1,1,1,0,'',5,600010);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (662,1532,86447,1596,3,48,'N','',0,0,'Ikky','ikky','','U','',20,2,57.3845,'','','Neutral','kaliri, Spires of Arak','Air (flies alongside flying mount)','Wing flutter (constant); vocalizations (on-click)','Idles about.','','N','','N','N','Y','N','N','N','N','N',0,'ikky.jpg','','wow64/icons/inv/feather/01.png','','','Kaliri hatchlings feast on grubs when they\'re young, and eventually graduate to anything smaller than themselves.','|cFFFFD200Quest:|r Ikky\'s Egg|n|cFFFFD200Zone:|r Spires of Arak','inline	Ikky\'s Egg	Ikky [97]\nzones	Spires of Arak	Spires of Arak\nlink	Ikky	http://wod.wowhead.com/quest=34898','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Quest:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/quest=34898\" target=\"_blank\">Ikky</a> [97]</p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Zone:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"/wow-pets/map/ikky/spires_of_arak/\" class=\"zonewithpets\">Spires of Arak</a></p>','N','','To obtain this pet, players must first pick up the quest <a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/quest=34838\" target=\"_blank\">Ikky\'s Egg</a> and complete the short quest chain that follows. Upon returning to the quest hub, Veil Terokk, players can complete the quest that will automatically teach the pet.','Y','Y','N',1370,1,3,'Y',919,2,8,'N',581,4,3,'Y',184,10,3,'Y',517,15,3,'Y',190,20,3,'Y',0,0,319,637,350,318,0,'2014-10-14 00:00:00',1,1,1,0,'',5,600010);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (663,1533,86532,0,2,39,'N','',0,172998,'Lanticore Spawnling','lanticore-spawnling','Lanticore Spawnling','U','blue',40,3,12.5956,'','U','Neutral','hydra, chimaeron, Searing Gorge, Burning Steppes','Ground','Vocalizations (on-click)','Idles about and occasionally its heads fight with each other.','','N','','N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',0,'lanticore-spawnling.jpg','wow64/icons/achievement/dungeon/blackwingdescent_raid_chimaron.png','wow64/icons/achievement/dungeon/blackwingdescent_raid_chimaron.png','','Right Click to summon and dismiss your Lanticore Spawnling.','No one knows what deep part of Blackwing Descent the Lanticore was kept in, but it probably smelled pretty awful.','|cFFFFD200Drop:|r The Lanticore|n|cFFFFD200Zone:|r Upper Black Rock Spire','add	2	Drop Rate: 1 in 1\nappend	0	[??+]\nlink	The Lanticore	http://wod.wowhead.com/npc=77081\ninline	Upper Black Rock Spire	Upper Blackrock Spire','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Drop:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/npc=77081\" target=\"_blank\">The Lanticore</a> [??+]</p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Zone:</span>&nbsp;Upper Blackrock Spire</p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Drop Rate:</span>&nbsp;1 in 1</p>','N','','The Lanticore Spawnling drops off a rare elite mob in the revamped, level 100 Heroic version of Upper Blackrock Spire.<br><br>The Lanticore mob can sometimes be found in the Rookery of the five-man dungeon, but is not a guaranteed spawn.<br><br>Although developer Jeremy Feasel <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Muffinus/status/517420777906245633\" target=\"_blank\">confirmed</a> that the pet is a 100% drop, it should be noted that <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Muffinus/status/549361090635644928\" target=\"_blank\">drop rates are different</a> when loot is set to Personal versus Group loot.','Y','Y','N',355,1,8,'Y',607,2,2,'Y',611,4,2,'N',594,10,2,'Y',447,15,6,'Y',538,20,8,'Y',0,0,378,522,336,225,0,'2014-10-14 00:00:00',1,1,1,0,'',5,600010);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (664,1538,86717,1538,3,109,'N','',0,173543,'Umbrafen Spore','umbrafen-spore','Umbrafen Spore','U','green',20,2,43.0976,'','P','Neutral','Shadowmoon Valley (Draenor)','Ground (hovers)','None','Spins in place and generates yellow dust particles.','','N','','N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',0,'umbrafen-spore.jpg','wow64/icons/priest/icon/chakra_blue.png','wow64/icons/priest/icon/chakra_blue.png','','Summon and dismiss your Umbrafen Spore.','The deep blue Umbrafen would later become home to a tribe of Broken.','|cFFFFD200Drop:|r Strange Spore|n|cFFFFD200Zone:|r Shadowmoon Valley|n','append	1	(Draenor)\nadd	2	Drop Rate: 1 in 1\nlink	Strange Spore	http://wod.wowhead.com/quest=35600\nzones	Shadowmoon Valley (Draenor)	Shadowmoon Valley (Draenor)','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Drop:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/quest=35600\" target=\"_blank\">Strange Spore</a></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Zone:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"/wow-pets/map/umbrafen-spore/shadowmoon_valley_draenor_/\" class=\"zonewithpets\">Shadowmoon Valley (Draenor)</a></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Drop Rate:</span>&nbsp;1 in 1</p>','N','','The Strange Spore can be found on top of a large mushroom in the mushroom field next to Elodor in northern Shadowmoon Valley (Draenor).<br><br>\r\nBy following the main path through Elodar that leads to Exarch\'s Rise and then continue climbing the mountain behind this point, players can jump down to the mushroom where the spore is located.<br><br>Players can loot the Strange Spore in Shadowmoon Valley (Draenor) only once per character.','Y','Y','N',632,1,3,'Y',315,2,2,'Y',746,4,7,'Y',743,10,4,'Y',1015,15,1,'N',282,20,10,'Y',0,0,280,393,272,199,0,'2014-10-14 00:00:00',1,1,1,0,'',5,600010);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (665,1540,86719,1538,3,109,'N','',0,173547,'Brilliant Spore','brilliant-spore','Brilliant Spore','U','green',20,2,56.2778,'','P','Neutral','Spires of Arak','Ground (hovers)','None','Spins in place and generates yellow dust particles.','','N','','N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',0,'brilliant-spore.jpg','wow64/icons/inv/elemental/primal_shadow.png','wow64/icons/inv/elemental/primal_shadow.png','','Summon and dismiss your Brilliant Spore.','Brilliant spores are very rarely seen, found deep under the waves of Draenor within the darkest corners of the Zangar fungal encroachment.','|cFFFFD200Drop:|r Rotcap|n|cFFFFD200Zone:|r Spires of Arak','add	2	Drop Rate: 1 in 1\nappend	0	[97]\nlink	Rotcap	http://wod.wowhead.com/npc=85504\nzones	Spires of Arak	Spires of Arak','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Drop:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/npc=85504\" target=\"_blank\">Rotcap</a> [97]</p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Zone:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"/wow-pets/map/brilliant-spore/spires_of_arak/\" class=\"zonewithpets\">Spires of Arak</a></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Drop Rate:</span>&nbsp;1 in 1</p>','N','','Players can loot the Brilliant Spore from this rarespawn only once per character.','Y','Y','N',186,1,3,'Y',315,2,2,'Y',746,4,7,'Y',743,10,4,'Y',1015,15,1,'N',282,20,10,'Y',0,0,283,1235,269,685,0,'2014-10-14 00:00:00',1,1,1,0,'',5,600010);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (666,1541,86879,0,9,122,'N','',0,170273,'Hydraling','hydraling','Hydraling','U','blue',20,3,42.7397,'','P','Neutral','Spires of Arak','Ground','Pit-pattering footsteps; vocalizations (on-click)','Idles about and occasionally its heads fight with each other.','','N','','N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',0,'hydraling.jpg','wow64/icons/trade/archaeology/whitehydrafigurine.png','wow64/icons/trade/archaeology/whitehydrafigurine.png','','','The hydraling can be an expensive pet, as it is capable of eating from three food bowls at the same time.','|cFFFFD200Drop:|r Vasha\'s Egg|n|cFFFFD200Zone:|r Spires of Arak','add	2	Drop Rate: 1 in 1\nappend	1	[96-98]\ninline	Vasha\'s Egg	Varasha\'s Egg\nzones	Spires of Arak	Spires of Arak\nlink	Varasha\'s Egg	http://wod.wowhead.com/object=232167','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Drop:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/object=232167\" target=\"_blank\">Varasha\'s Egg</a></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Zone:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"/wow-pets/map/hydraling/spires_of_arak/\" class=\"zonewithpets\">Spires of Arak</a> [96-98]</p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Drop Rate:</span>&nbsp;1 in 1</p>','N','','Varasha\'s Egg is located in an underground cave in The Writhing Mire in Spires of Arak. The entrance to the cave is located on the largest island in the swamp area.<br><br> Upon reaching the bottom of the cave, players will find a nest under a pillar of light with Varasha\'s Egg inside. Clicking on the egg will spawn the rarespawn Varasha, who will come charging down the cave entrance. Varasha must be defeated first before her egg can be looted.<br><br>Players can loot the pet from Varasha\'s Egg only once per character.','Y','Y','N',1372,1,9,'Y',204,2,10,'Y',1380,4,8,'N',424,10,9,'Y',276,15,9,'Y',513,20,9,'Y',0,0,380,665,348,309,0,'2014-10-14 00:00:00',1,1,1,0,'',5,600010);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (667,1542,87111,1530,8,10,'N','',0,170281,'Frostwolf Pup','frostwolf-pup','Frostwolf Pup','U','blue',30,3,26.4315,'rep','P','Horde','Ashran','Ground','Vocalizations (on-click)','Sniffs the ground and scratches itself.','','N','','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',0,'frostwolf-pup.jpg','wow64/icons/inv/frostwolfpup.png','wow64/icons/inv/pet/frostwolfpup.png','','','These pups are bundles of fur and teeth until they grow up, at which point they are really just teeth.','|cFFFFD200Vendor:|r Beska Redtusk|n|cFFFFD200Faction:|r Frostwolf|n|n','remove	1	\nadd	1	Zone: Warspear\nadd	2	Faction: Frostwolf Orcs - Revered\nadd	3	Cost: 1000|TINTERFACE\\MONEYFRAME\\UI-GOLDICON.BLP:0|t 2000|TINTERFACE\\ICONS\\inv_apexis_draenor.blp:0|t (unlimited supply)\nzones	Warspear	Warspear\nlink	Beska Redtusk	http://wod.wowhead.com/npc=86036','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Vendor:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/npc=86036\" target=\"_blank\">Beska Redtusk</a></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Zone:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"/wow-pets/map/frostwolf-pup/warspear/\" class=\"zonewithpets\">Warspear</a></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Faction:</span>&nbsp;Frostwolf Orcs - Revered</p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Cost:</span>&nbsp;1000<img src=\"/images/wow16/moneyframe/ui-goldicon.png\" style=\"vertical-align:middle;\" alt=\"gold\" title=\"gold\"/> 2000<img src=\"/images/wow16/icons/inv/apexis/draenor.png\" style=\"vertical-align:middle;\" alt=\"Apexis Crystal\" title=\"Apexis Crystal\"/> (unlimited supply)</p>','N','','Players can earn Revered with the Frostwolf Orcs faction by completing all related quests, however it is also possible to earn reputation by killing level 100 mobs in Frostfire Ridge. Areas include: Magnarok, Iron Siege Works, and just northeast of Daggermaw Ravine.','Y','Y','N',110,1,8,'Y',165,2,5,'N',345,4,8,'Y',360,10,5,'Y',362,15,8,'N',997,20,8,'Y',0,0,426,822,343,380,0,'2014-10-14 00:00:00',1,1,1,0,'',5,600010);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (668,1543,87257,0,5,35,'N','',0,177216,'Pygmy Cow','pygmy-cow','Glass of Warm Milk','U','blue',30,3,22.4826,'','P','Neutral','garrison, Shadowmoon Valley (Draenor), Frostfire Ridge','Ground','Pit-pattering footsteps; vocalizations (on-click)','Idles about.','','N','','N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',0,'pygmy-cow.jpg','wow64/icons/inv/drink/milk_01.png','wow64/icons/spell/nature/polymorph_cow.png','','','Originally bred to make milk more palatable for gnomes.','|cFFFFD200Drop:|r Garrisons, Barn, Level 3','add	1	Zone: Lunarfall, Frostwall\nadd	2	Drop Rate: 1 in 1\ninline	Garrisons, Barn, Level 3	Glass of Warm Milk\nlink	Glass of Warm Milk	http://wod.wowhead.com/object=239171\nzones	Lunarfall	Lunarfall\nzones	Frostwall	Frostwall','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Drop:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/object=239171\" target=\"_blank\">Glass of Warm Milk</a></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Zone:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"/wow-pets/map/pygmy-cow/lunarfall/\" class=\"zonewithpets\">Lunarfall</a>, <a href=\"/wow-pets/map/pygmy-cow/frostwall/\" class=\"zonewithpets\">Frostwall</a></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Drop Rate:</span>&nbsp;1 in 1</p>','N','','The Pygmy Cow can only be looted from a level 3 Barn in the garrison.<br><br>A brown wooden mug will spawn on either the first or second floor of the Barn; it does not have the standard container \"glow\". Hovering over it with the mouse cursor will highlight it, however.<br><br>Players will need to get creative to reach the second floor of a level 3 Barn, as there is no direct path up and flying in Draenor is not possible. Using Goblin Gliders or the <a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/item=114633\" target=\"_blank\">XD-57 \"Bullseye\" Guided Rocket Kit</a> (from the level 2 Gnomish Gearworks or Goblin Workshop) are two possible ways, but there may be many other methods.<br><br>Players can loot the pet from the wooden mug only once per character.','Y','N','N',163,1,5,'Y',1402,2,8,'N',1401,4,8,'N',541,10,5,'Y',1016,15,8,'Y',1400,20,8,'Y',0,0,412,547,331,258,0,'2014-10-14 00:00:00',1,1,1,0,'',5,600010);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (669,1544,87669,0,7,40,'N','',0,170268,'Hatespark the Tiny','hatespark-the-tiny','Hatespark the Tiny','U','blue',40,3,18.4017,'','P','Neutral','fire elemental, anniversary','Ground','Vocalizations (on-click)','Idles about.','','N','WoW\'s 10th Anniversary','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N','N',0,'hatespark-the-tiny.jpg','wow64/icons/spell/fire/ragnaros_supernova.png','wow64/icons/spell/fire/ragnaros_supernova.png','','','His hate is not diminished by size.','|cFFFFD200Drop:|r Ragnaros the Firelord|n|cFFFFD200Zone:|r Molten Core (Anniversary Edition)','remove	0	\nremove	0	\nadd	0	Vendor: Auction House','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Vendor:</span>&nbsp;Auction House</p>','N','','WoW celebrated its 10th anniversary in 2014, and as part of the celebration a special version of the Molten Core raid was released.<br><br>Players were able to queue up for this revamped, level 100 raid through the Looking For Raid window during the anniversary period.<br><br>Hatespark the Tiny originally dropped from the last boss, Ragnaros.<br><br>This pet can now be found only through trades and the Auction House.','Y','Y','N',472,1,6,'Y',179,2,7,'Y',503,4,7,'Y',1407,10,7,'Y',173,15,7,'N',1025,20,10,'N',0,0,436,762,377,388,0,'2014-10-14 00:00:00',1,1,1,0,'',5,600010);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (670,1546,87705,1545,3,53,'N','',0,170289,'Stormwing','stormwing','Stormwing','U','blue',30,3,25.3553,'','P','Neutral','blue bird, achievement','Air (flies alongside flying mount)','Wing flutter (constant); vocalizations (on-click)','Idles about.','','N','','N','N','N','N','Y','N','N','N',0,'stormwing.jpg','wow64/icons/ability/mount/stormcrowmount.png','wow64/icons/ability/mount/stormcrowmount.png','','','Half bird, half elemental, the beautiful Stormwing is truly capable of shock and awe.','|cFFFFD200Achievement:|r So. Many. Pets.','add	1	Category: Collect\nlink	So. Many. Pets.	http://wod.wowhead.com/achievement=9643','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Achievement:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/achievement=9643\" target=\"_blank\">So. Many. Pets.</a></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Category:</span>&nbsp;Collect</p>','N','','This pet is rewarded via the mail when your character completes the \"So. Many. Pets.\" achievement. To complete this achievement, your character must possess at least 600 unique <a href=\"/wow.pets/index.asp\">vanity pets</a>. Upon learning your 600th pet, you\'ll immediately receive this pet in your mailbox.','Y','N','Y',504,1,3,'Y',204,2,10,'Y',779,4,7,'Y',184,10,3,'Y',170,15,3,'Y',581,20,3,'Y',0,0,434,557,381,298,0,'2014-10-14 00:00:00',1,1,1,0,'',5,600010);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (671,1563,7546,57,2,36,'N','',0,10699,'Bronze Whelpling','bronze-whelpling','Time-Locked Box','U','blue',30,3,27.5347,'','U','Neutral','orange dragon, Blasted Lands','Air (flies alongside flying mount)','<p>Wing flutter (constant); vocalizations (on-click)</p>','<p>Flutters about and spins around.</p>','','N','','N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',0,'bronze-whelpling.jpg','wow64/icons/inv/eng/crate2.png','wow64/icons/inv/misc/head_dragon_bronze.png','','Right Click to summon and dismiss your whelpling.','The Bronze Whelpling was lost in time until an unusual event allowed her to escape.','|cFFFFD200Drop: |rIron Horde|n|cFFFFD200Zone: |rBlasted Lands','append	1	[90+]\nadd	2	Approximate Drop Rate: 1 in 100\nremove	0	\nadd	0	Drop: Ironmarch Orcs [90]\nzones	Blasted Lands	Blasted Lands\nlink	Ironmarch Orcs	http://wod.wowhead.com/npc=76556','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Drop:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/npc=76556\" target=\"_blank\">Ironmarch Orcs</a> [90]</p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Zone:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"/wow-pets/map/bronze-whelpling/blasted_lands/\" class=\"zonewithpets\">Blasted Lands</a> [90+]</p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Approximate Drop Rate:</span>&nbsp;1 in 100</p>','N','','The Bronze Whelpling was implemented during the 6.0 patch leading up to the expansion, Warlords of Draenor.<br><br>\r\nPlayers can find Iron Horde throughout the revamped level 90 portion of Blasted Lands. Any of the Ironmarch orcs has a chance to drop the pet.','Y','Y','N',1353,1,6,'Y',405,2,7,'Y',170,4,3,'Y',122,10,2,'Y',569,15,8,'N',589,20,6,'Y',0,0,369,1428,350,860,0,'2014-10-14 00:00:00',1,1,1,0,'',4,112010);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (672,1564,88103,0,7,43,'N','',0,170272,'Doom Bloom','doom-bloom','Doom Bloom','U','blue',20,3,51.3325,'','P','Neutral','Gorgrond','Ground','Vocalizations (on-click)','Idles about and occasionally its heads fight with each other.','','N','','N','Y','N','N','N','N','N','N',0,'doom-bloom.jpg','wow64/icons/inv/misc/herb_dreamingglory.png','wow64/icons/inv/misc/herb_dreamingglory.png','','','A clear indication why goblin fertilizers should be used sparingly.','|cFFFFD200Drop:|r Mandrakor|n|cFFFFD200Location:|r Gorgrond|n','append	0	[93]\nremove	1	\nadd	1	Zone: Gorgrond\nadd	2	Drop Rate: 1 in 1\nlink	Mandrakor	http://wod.wowhead.com/npc=84406\nzones	Gorgrond	Gorgrond','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Drop:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/npc=84406\" target=\"_blank\">Mandrakor</a> [93]</p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Zone:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"/wow-pets/map/doom-bloom/gorgrond/\" class=\"zonewithpets\">Gorgrond</a></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Drop Rate:</span>&nbsp;1 in 1</p>','N','','Mandrakor is a rarespawn located in a cave east of Gronn Canyon and northwest of Highpass.<br><br>Players can loot the pet from this rarespawn only once per character.<br><br> Read more about this pet in our <a href=\"http://www.warcraftpets.com/news/doom-bloom-pet-of-the-month-may-2016/\">Pet of the Month</a>!','Y','Y','N',394,1,7,'Y',665,2,4,'N',402,4,7,'Y',110,10,8,'Y',123,15,9,'N',400,20,7,'Y',0,0,366,915,306,423,0,'2014-10-14 00:00:00',1,1,1,0,'',5,600010);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (673,1566,88222,1572,3,108,'N','',0,176137,'Everbloom Peachick','everbloom-peachick','Everbloom Peachick','U','blue',20,3,50.0347,'','U','Neutral','peacock, garrison, Shadowmoon Valley (Draenor), Frostfire Ridge','Ground','Vocalizations (on-click)','Pecks the ground and idles about.','','N','','N','N','Y','N','N','N','N','N',0,'everbloom-peachick.jpg','wow64/icons/inv/pet/peacock_green.png','wow64/icons/inv/pet/peacock_green.png','','Right Click to summon and dismiss your Everbloom Peachick.','These tiny creatures seem to favor big, fluffy nests, preferably atop an animal-loving dryad.','|cFFFFD200Quest:|r For The Birds','append	0	[100]\nadd	1	Zone: The Everbloom\nlink	For The Birds	http://wod.wowhead.com/quest=37150','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Quest:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/quest=37150\" target=\"_blank\">For The Birds</a> [100]</p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Zone:</span>&nbsp;The Everbloom</p>','N','','The quest that rewards this pet can only be picked up and turned in at the Lunarfall Inn (A) or Frostwall Tavern (H) in a player\'s garrison. \r\nDifferent NPCs will visit the Inn or Tavern and offer a dungeon quest each day.','Y','Y','N',184,1,3,'Y',521,2,3,'N',186,4,3,'Y',112,10,3,'Y',188,15,3,'N',524,20,3,'Y',0,0,410,830,327,389,0,'2014-10-14 00:00:00',1,1,1,0,'',5,600010);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (674,1568,88300,0,9,8,'N','',0,170279,'Puddle Terror','puddle-terror','Puddle Terror','U','blue',20,3,39.5987,'','P','Neutral','water elemental, garrison, Shadowmoon Valley (Draenor), Frostfire Ridge','Ground','Running water (constant); vocalizations (on-click)','Idles about.','','N','','N','N','Y','N','N','N','N','N',0,'puddle-terror.jpg','wow64/icons/inv/pet/pettrap02.png','wow64/icons/ability/shawaterelemental/reform.png','','','Living so closely to the water\'s surface, the puddle terror is not only friend to all aquatic creatures, it is one.','|cFFFFD200Quest:|r Mastering the Menagerie','add	1	Zone: Lunarfall, Frostwall\nadd	2	\nadd	3	Drop: Big Bag of Pet Supplies\nadd	4	Approximate Drop Rate: 1 in 50\nappend	0	[??]\nlink	Mastering the Menagerie	http://wod.wowhead.com/quest=37644\nlink	Big Bag of Pet Supplies	http://wod.wowhead.com/item=118697\nzones	Lunarfall	Lunarfall\nzones	Frostwall	Frostwall','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Quest:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/quest=37644\" target=\"_blank\">Mastering the Menagerie</a> [??]</p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Zone:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"/wow-pets/map/puddle-terror/lunarfall/\" class=\"zonewithpets\">Lunarfall</a>, <a href=\"/wow-pets/map/puddle-terror/frostwall/\" class=\"zonewithpets\">Frostwall</a></p>\n<p class=\'empty\'>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Drop:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/item=118697\" target=\"_blank\">Big Bag of Pet Supplies</a></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Approximate Drop Rate:</span>&nbsp;1 in 50</p>','N','','The Mastering the Menagerie daily quest is only available at a level 3 Menagerie inside your garrison. To upgrade your Menagerie you must complete the achievement <a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/achievement=9463\" target=\"_blank\">Draenic Pet Battler</a> to unlock the level 3 blueprints, and have a level 3 garrison (requires level 100).\r\n<br><br>Once the Menagerie has been upgraded to level 3, Mastering the Menagerie will replace the previous daily from the level 1 and 2 Menagerie (<a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/quest=36483\" target=\"_blank\">Battle Pet Roundup</a> or <a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/quest=36662\" target=\"_blank\">Scrappin\'</a>).','Y','Y','N',118,1,9,'Y',574,2,7,'N',404,4,7,'Y',111,10,1,'Y',350,15,1,'N',564,20,9,'Y',0,0,405,507,350,253,0,'2014-10-14 00:00:00',1,1,1,0,'',5,600010);
