a level 3 garrison (requires level 100).\r\n<br><br>Once the Menagerie has been upgraded to level 3, Mastering the Menagerie will replace the previous daily from the level 1 and 2 Menagerie (<a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/quest=36483\" target=\"_blank\">Battle Pet Roundup</a> or <a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/quest=36662\" target=\"_blank\">Scrappin\'</a>).','Y','Y','N',1273,1,4,'Y',665,2,4,'N',663,4,4,'Y',499,10,4,'Y',780,15,4,'Y',762,20,1,'Y',0,0,396,544,372,330,0,'2014-10-14 00:00:00',1,1,1,0,'',5,600010);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (689,1395,78895,0,6,69,'N','',0,159296,'Lil\' Leftovers','lil-leftovers','Leftovers','U','blue',30,3,20.0478,'','P','Neutral','cooking','Ground','Bubbling (constant); vocalizations (on-click)','Bubbles and idles about.','','N','','N','N','N','Y','N','N','N','N',0,'lil-leftovers.jpg','wow64/icons/achievement/cooking/masterofthepot.png','wow64/icons/inv/misc/forkandknife.png','','Summons or dismisses Lil\' Leftovers.','Cute enough to eat, but not recommended.','|cFFFFD200Profession:|r Cooking','add	1	Approximate Drop Rate: Unknown','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Profession:</span>&nbsp;Cooking</p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Approximate Drop Rate:</span>&nbsp;Unknown</p>','N','','Players with the cooking profession have a chance to craft this pet when cooking <a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/spells=9.185?filter=cr=20:16;crs=1:6;crv=0:0\" target=\"_blank\">Draenor recipes</a>.<br><br>When attempting to feed this pet a Magical Mini-Treat or Magical Pet Biscuit, an error message will appear: \"Food cannot eat food.\"<br><br> Read more about this pet in our <a href=\"http://www.warcraftpets.com/news/lil-leftovers-pet-of-the-month-november-2016/\">Pet of the Month</a>!','Y','Y','N',449,1,4,'Y',527,2,5,'N',941,4,1,'N',541,10,5,'Y',165,15,5,'N',580,20,5,'N',0,0,320,553,316,237,0,'2014-10-14 00:00:00',1,1,1,0,'',5,600010);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (690,1403,79410,1470,3,104,'N','',0,160403,'Mechanical Axebeak','mechanical-axebeak','Mechanical Axebeak','U','blue',20,3,44.9418,'','U','Neutral','toucan, engineering, garrison, Shadowmoon Valley (Draenor), Frostfire Ridge','Air (flies alongside flying mount)','Wing flutter (constant); vocalizations (on-click)','Idles about.','','N','','N','N','N','Y','N','N','N','N',0,'mechanical-axebeak.jpg','wow64/icons/inv/box/birdcage_01.png','wow64/icons/inv/box/birdcage_01.png','','Summons and dismisses your Mechanical Axebeak.','Squeeeeeeeawk!','|cFFFFD200Profession: |rEngineering','append	0	[1]\nadd	1	Taught By: [Schematic: Mechanical Axebeak]\nlink	Schematic: Mechanical Axebeak	http://wod.wowhead.com/item=118484','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Profession:</span>&nbsp;Engineering [1]</p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Taught By:</span>&nbsp;[<a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/item=118484\" target=\"_blank\">Schematic: Mechanical Axebeak</a>]</p>','N','','Players with the engineering skill can purchase the schematic for this pet at the Engineering Works plot in the garrison or from the engineering vendor at the Alliance or Horde faction hub in Ashran. The schematic costs one <a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/item=119299\" target=\"_blank\">Secret of Draenor Engineering</a>; crafting this currency has a one day cooldown.\r\n<br><br>Non-engineers can also craft this pet by building the Engineering Works in the garrison, and upgrading the plot to level 3. After obtaining enough materials, speak with one of the NPCs at the level 3 Engineering Works to have them create the pet for you.','Y','Y','N',504,1,3,'Y',521,2,3,'N',334,4,10,'N',112,10,3,'Y',916,15,10,'Y',170,20,3,'Y',0,0,342,471,337,237,0,'2014-10-14 00:00:00',1,1,1,0,'',5,600010);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (691,1411,80101,1572,3,108,'N','',0,161643,'Royal Peachick','royal-peacock','Royal Peacock','U','blue',30,3,29.9036,'','P','Neutral','peacock, achievement','Ground','Vocalizations (on-click)','Pecks the ground and idles about.','','N','','N','N','N','N','Y','N','N','N',0,'royal-peacock.jpg','wow64/icons/inv/pet/peacock_gold.png','wow64/icons/inv/pet/peacock_gold.png','','Right Click to summon and dismiss your royal peacock.','A single peacock feather is often laid upon a grave to ward off evil spirits.','|cFFFFD200Achievement:|r Draenor Safari|n','add	1	Category: Collect\nlink	Draenor Safari	http://wod.wowhead.com/achievement=9685','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Achievement:</span>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/achievement=9685\" target=\"_blank\">Draenor Safari</a></p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Category:</span>&nbsp;Collect</p>','N','','This pet is rewarded via the mail when your character completes the \"Draenor Safari\" achievement. To complete this achievement, your character must capture at least one of each wild pet unique to Draenor. Upon capturing the final pet, you\'ll immediately receive this pet in your mailbox.','Y','N','Y',184,1,3,'Y',366,2,5,'N',1062,4,9,'N',1370,10,3,'Y',589,15,6,'Y',568,20,8,'N',0,0,412,459,332,225,0,'2014-10-14 00:00:00',1,1,1,0,'',5,600010);
INSERT INTO `pets_defs` VALUES (692,1426,82464,0,6,71,'N','',0,166071,'Elekk Plushie','elekk-plushie','Elekk Plushie','U','white',20,1,41.7182,'','P','Neutral','tailoring, garrison, Shadowmoon Valley (Draenor), Frostfire Ridge','Ground (stationary)','Vocalizations (on-click)','None.','','N','','N','N','N','Y','N','N','N','N',0,'elekk-plushie.jpg','wow64/icons/inv/tailoring/elekkplushie.png','wow64/icons/inv/tailoring/elekkplushie.png','','Right Click to summon and dismiss your Elekk Plushie.','This adorable little elephant is always there for you.','|cFFFFD200Profession:|r Tailoring|n','append	0	[1]\nadd	1	Taught By: [Recipe: Elekk Plushie]\nlink	Recipe: Elekk Plushie	http://wod.wowhead.com/item=114865','<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Profession:</span>&nbsp;Tailoring [1]</p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#FFD200;\">Taught By:</span>&nbsp;[<a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/item=114865\" target=\"_blank\">Recipe: Elekk Plushie</a>]</p>','N','','Players with the tailoring skill can purchase the recipe for this pet at the Tailoring Emporium plot in the garrison or from the tailoring vendor at the Alliance or Horde faction hub in Ashran. The recipe costs five <a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/item=118722\" target=\"_blank\">Secret of Draenor Tailoring</a>; crafting this currency has a one day cooldown.<br><br> The Elekk Plushie is part of the achievement \"<a href=\"http://wod.wowhead.com/achievement=9069\" target=\"_blank\">An Awfully Big Adventure</a>\" which rewards the pet <a href=\"/go.asp?pet=trunks\">Trunks</a>.<br><br>To complete this achievement, players must battle trainers with the Elekk Plushie on their team. Because the plushie doesn\'t have any actual damaging attacks, it\'s considered a \"carry pet\". However, its large health pool at max level does allow it to soak some hits.<br><br>The Elekk Plushie does not have to be swapped into battle for one round to count towards the achievement. It can happily sit on the back row and only needs to be on the team during the encounter.','Y','Y','N',1335,1,6,'N',1345,2,1,'N',1334,4,6,'N',1347,10,5,'N',1336,15,1,'N',1337,20,1,'N',0,0,420,1205,223,771,0,'2014-10-14 00:00:00',1,1,1,0,'',5,600010);
